The last Holden Commodore ever, like everything else from Australia, is seemingly out to kill you . The Last Holden Commodore Ever Might Be A Big Nasty ZR1-Powered Hell Sedan The Last Holden Commodore Ever Might Be A Big Nasty ZR1-Powered Hell Sedan The Last Holden Commodore Ever Might Be A Big… There’s a maybe-supercharged V8 explosion coming from the southern shores of wonder, a ZR1-familiar … Read more Read more 
The Holden Special Vehicles Commodore GTSR W1 does come with the Corvette ZR1's supercharged LS9 engine, cranking out 636 horsepower. It also comes with a 6-speed manual. Advertisement Advertisement 
Why is Chevrolet killing Holden, again? And the American-sold Chevy SS along with it? Why? Dumb reasons. 
The people with upside-down accents at CarAdvice already got to drive it. They hit a bird on the track, though :(.
